{'relation': ['https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48475/', 'https://cesf.pitt.edu'], 'title': ['The Future of Nonprofits: Leveraging Technology and Regional Networks for Transformative, Regenerative Impact'], 'creator': ['Brown, Fred', 'Francis, Emily'], 'description': ['Technology is reshaping how nonprofits operate, connect, and scale their impact, recognizing that the goal of their work is to move our region from surviving to thriving. This discussion will highlight emerging tools, regional networks, and strategic approaches to maximizing the role of AI, data, and digital transformation in the nonprofit sector are made possible through The Forbes Funds’ Sixth Pivot.  \r\n\r\nHelp your organization move beyond crisis response and short-term fixes to build enduring, strategic collaborations. We’ll explore the role of coaching, point-in-time capacity-building, and leadership development in ensuring long-term resilience. Nonprofits and their partners must rethink how they invest in capacity building, leadership, and technology. This discussion will highlight best practices in strategic investment, regional network-building, and ecosystem development for long-term sustainability.'], 'date': ['2025-03-04'], 'type': ['Conference or Workshop Item', 'PeerReviewed'], 'format': ['application/vnd.ms-powerpoint', 'application/pdf'], 'language': ['en', 'en'], 'rights': [None, None], 'identifier': ['https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48475/1/TFF_University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20AI%20Presentation%20March-2025.pptx', 'https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48475/2/TFF_University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20AI%20Presentation%20March-2025.pdf', '  Brown, Fred and Francis, Emily  (2025) The Future of Nonprofits: Leveraging Technology and Regional Networks for Transformative, Regenerative Impact.  In: 2025 Community Engaged Scholarship Forum, March 4, 2025, William Pitt Union, University of Pittsburgh.    (Unpublished)  ']}